<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How This Fits Into Tomato Grafting</h2>

  <p>
    Clips are only one part of the process, but they are one of the most common failure points. Even with good cuts and healing conditions, poor clip fit can cause subtle movement that prevents proper union.
  </p>

  <p>
    Simplifying your setup — including using forgiving clip types — helps reduce those failure points.
  </p>

